      <div id="govspeak">
        <p>You can take up to 25% of your pension pot in cash as a tax-free lump sum. Most pension scheme offers this.</p>

        <p>After that you pay Income Tax on income that’s above your tax-free Personal Allowance. This is currently £10,000 for anyone born after 5 April 1948 and with an income under £100,000.</p>

        <p>If you were born before then or your income is higher you get a different <a href="www.gov.uk/income-tax-rates/personal-allowances">Personal Allowance</a>.</p>

        <p>If you’re blind you might also get <a href="www.gov.uk/blind-persons-allowance">Blind Person’s Allowance</a></p>

